trend_summary: Over the series, the mainly rural landscape shows steady cropland enlargement, especially east and south, at the expense of contiguous forest blocks. The central township spreads slightly outward and infills along the main northeast-southwest roadway, yet overall built footprint stays low. Forest patches thin but remain dominant; few new facilities emerge in the southeast.
notable_changes: Cropland fields expand markedly on the eastern and southern margins.
Several forest blocks in the north and centre shrink or fragment, indicating ongoing clearing.
Incremental housing and small-lot development radiate from the central town core.
Linear roadside ribbon development appears along the main diagonal highway.
A compact new facility/compound is established near the southeastern tip.
